# Prompt Anatomy MVP — Core Rules



## Project identity



Building the **Prompt Anatomy ecosystem site** — a static React MVP deployed at **https://promptanatomy.site** (repo: **github.com/DITreneris/site**, host: **Vercel**). Showcases 8 domains, an interactive Anatomizer, and a team AI maturity quiz.



## Non-negotiables



- **Document map:** `DOCS_INDEX.md` — task router, agent roster, skills catalog, file registry. Update it when adding docs, agents, or skills.

- **Content source:** `primal_concept.txt` defines domain names, roles, audiences, and messaging. Do not rename domains or invent new ecosystem stages.

- **UI source of truth:** `src/index.css` (`@theme` + `@utility`) and `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` §14. `snippet.txt` is legacy only — do not reintroduce its slate-950/indigo/rainbow palette.

- **URL model:** canonical/OG/sitemap → `promptanatomy.site`; Organization/platform CTAs → `promptanatomy.app`.

- **Ecosystem order:** Enter → Use → Create → Hire → Manage → Decide → Deepen → Play (plus core hub at promptanatomy.app).



## Scope discipline



MVP = marketing/demo site only. No auth, CMS, backend, or payment flows unless explicitly requested.



## Code style



- TypeScript + React functional components

- Extract data to `src/data/`, UI to `src/components/`

- Tailwind utility classes; avoid custom CSS unless necessary

- Minimize diff size; no drive-by refactors



## Brand voice



Professional, direct, systems-oriented. Avoid casual AI hype ("game-changing", "delighted", filler pleasantries). Emphasize structure, repeatability, and operational clarity.



## Before finishing any task



- Verify changes work in dev (`npm run dev`)

- Ensure `npm run build` passes (includes `generate:og` prebuild)

- After layout changes, run `npm run qa:viewport`

- Ensure mobile responsiveness is not regressed

- Keep external domain links correct (`promptanatomy.app` for platform CTAs, etc.)

- Record user-visible changes in `CHANGELOG.md` under `## [Unreleased]` (Keep a Changelog format). Delegate to the `changelog-keeper` agent, or update it directly for small changes. Skip only for no-op/internal-only edits.

